<doc id="1137010" wikidata="Q7932925" url="?curid=1137010" title="Vinyl (Dramarama album)">
<text>Vinyl is the fourth album by alternative rock group Dramarama, released in 1991. It is a celebration of classic rock with Mick Taylor, formerly of The Rolling Stones, playing guitar on all tracks, including, ironically, a Stones song. 

==Critical reception==
&quot;Alternative Rock&quot; wrote that the sound of the album was &quot;steeped in the Southern rock tradition of R&amp;B riffery, bluesy guitar leads, and a whiff of C&amp;W.&quot;

