=== Volume of a spherical cap with a curved base ===

The volume of a spherical cap with a curved base can be calculated by considering two spheres with radii formula_28 and formula_29, separated by some distance formula_39, and for which their surfaces intersect at formula_40. That is, the curvature of the base comes from sphere 2. The volume is thus the difference between sphere 2&#x27;s cap (with height formula_41) and sphere 1&#x27;s cap (with height formula_3),

