=== Surface area bounded by parallel disks ===

The curved surface area of the spherical segment bounded by two parallel disks is the difference of surface areas of their respective spherical caps. For a sphere of radius formula_1, and caps with heights formula_34 and formula_35, the area is

:formula_60

or, using geographic coordinates with latitudes formula_61 and formula_62,

